- Happy birthday to you - Happy birthday to you

36
00:03:40,719 --> 00:03:47,120
- Happy birthday to you - Happy birthday to you

37
00:03:47,120 --> 00:03:48,159
Thank you.

38
00:03:48,159 --> 00:03:49,520
- Happy birthday, my pretty mom. - Happy birthday.

39
00:03:49,520 --> 00:03:50,719
- May you be prettier and prettier. - Happy birthday.

40
00:03:50,719 --> 00:03:52,000
Thank you, baby.

41
00:03:52,960 --> 00:03:54,400
- Make a wish. - Okay.

42
00:04:03,919 --> 00:04:05,960
- Thank you. - Good.

43
00:04:06,479 --> 00:04:08,879
We're all here today.

44
00:04:09,080 --> 00:04:11,120
It's Shi Yi's mom's birthday again.

45
00:04:11,400 --> 00:04:12,400
What about this?

46
00:04:12,520 --> 00:04:15,039
Let me recite a poem to liven the atmosphere.

47
00:04:15,919 --> 00:04:17,480
- Okay. - Dad is reciting a poem again.

48
00:04:18,240 --> 00:04:20,560
Your dad is playing the poet today.

49
00:04:21,000 --> 00:04:22,000
Don't mess around.

50
00:04:22,319 --> 00:04:23,399
Listen carefully.

51
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:26,920
I haven't written a poem in years.

52
00:04:27,279 --> 00:04:28,560
Your compliment would be appreciated.

53
00:04:28,920 --> 00:04:30,519
Critique is not accepted though.

54
00:04:32,680 --> 00:04:36,759
"The day you got out of the car..."

55
00:04:39,050 --> 00:04:41,319
"and came to me,"

56
00:04:42,319 --> 00:04:47,279
"it was like you had thrown away the hard armor..."

57
00:04:48,279 --> 00:04:50,120
"and turned..."

58
00:04:51,079 --> 00:04:53,639
"into to a scaredy-cat."

59
00:04:54,170 --> 00:04:55,800
Mom, that's you.

60
00:04:56,639 --> 00:04:58,000
Who is a scaredy-cat?

61
00:04:59,199 --> 00:05:01,920
"At that moment I suspected..."

62
00:05:02,519 --> 00:05:05,560
"we were never apart,"

63
00:05:08,319 --> 00:05:13,439
"someone must have stolen my memories."

64
00:05:15,839 --> 00:05:17,759
"All these years while you were gone,"

65
00:05:19,079 --> 00:05:23,639
"my life was completely blank."

66
00:05:25,439 --> 00:05:27,720
"Every day is your birthday..."

67
00:05:28,839 --> 00:05:31,000
"for the rest of your life."

68
00:05:31,439 --> 00:05:34,040
"I'm going to say this every day."

69
00:05:34,959 --> 00:05:37,279
"Happy birthday."

70
00:05:38,120 --> 00:05:41,240
"Happy birthday,"

71
00:05:44,319 --> 00:05:46,480
"my dream of the night."

72
00:05:56,600 --> 00:05:57,639
Bravo.

73
00:05:59,639 --> 00:06:00,639
Bravo.

74
00:06:01,879 --> 00:06:03,240
Thank you.

75
00:06:03,759 --> 00:06:05,480
You're making me sound like an old hag.

76
00:06:05,839 --> 00:06:06,959
That's so cheesy.

77
00:06:07,120 --> 00:06:08,199
Are you going to eat or not?

78
00:06:11,959 --> 00:06:13,360
Let's take a family picture.

79
00:06:13,759 --> 00:06:14,920
- Okay, come on. - Come on.

80
00:06:14,920 --> 00:06:15,959
Excuse me.

81
00:06:15,959 --> 00:06:17,519
- Take a picture for us. - Let's take a picture.

82
00:06:17,759 --> 00:06:19,399
- Go over there. - Okay.

83
00:06:20,879 --> 00:06:21,959
Here.

84
00:06:22,360 --> 00:06:23,839
Take the cake along.

85
00:06:24,199 --> 00:06:25,240
Okay.

86
00:06:26,000 --> 00:06:27,319
Shi Yi, come here.

87
00:06:28,199 --> 00:06:30,160
Mom, I'll stand here. It's fine.

88
00:06:30,160 --> 00:06:31,480
- What's wrong? - Nothing.

89
00:06:31,480 --> 00:06:32,480
Are you hurt?

90
00:06:32,639 --> 00:06:33,639
No.

91
00:06:33,639 --> 00:06:35,480
You got hurt while protecting Hou Jue, right?

92
00:06:36,040 --> 00:06:37,120
- What's going on? - It's just a scratch.

93
00:06:37,120 --> 00:06:38,600
- It's okay. - If it's just a small wound,

94
00:06:38,600 --> 00:06:39,759
why does it still hurt so much?

95
00:06:39,759 --> 00:06:42,079
Listen, you can't be his bodyguard anymore.

96
00:06:42,079 --> 00:06:44,480
Do you hear me? You can't be a bodyguard anymore.

97
00:06:44,480 --> 00:06:45,480
- It's okay, Ms. Zhang. - Look at me.

98
00:06:45,480 --> 00:06:47,000
I can never agree to let you do this again.

99
00:06:47,000 --> 00:06:48,959
Let's take a picture. Look, they're waiting for us.

100
00:06:48,959 --> 00:06:50,000
Let's take a picture.

101
00:06:50,439 --> 00:06:51,839
- Do it quickly then. - Calm down.

102
00:06:54,839 --> 00:06:55,839
It's done.

103
00:06:55,839 --> 00:06:56,920
Okay.

104
00:06:57,120 --> 00:06:58,600
- Have a seat, Ms. Zhang. - Have a seat.

105
00:06:58,920 --> 00:07:01,160
I'm telling you, Shi Yi.

106
00:07:01,279 --> 00:07:04,319
You got hurt before this because you were an athlete.

107
00:07:04,319 --> 00:07:05,759
That was for the glory of the country.

108
00:07:05,759 --> 00:07:06,759
But this is different.

109
00:07:07,319 --> 00:07:08,639
You're risking your life for someone else's life.

110
00:07:08,839 --> 00:07:09,959
Why should you?

111
00:07:09,959 --> 00:07:12,199
Are our lives beneath anyone else's?

112
00:07:12,439 --> 00:07:13,879
- No, I... - Mom, no...

113
00:07:14,000 --> 00:07:15,240
- Ying Nan. - Don't interrupt.

114
00:07:15,839 --> 00:07:18,120
I thought even if Hou Jue causes trouble,

115
00:07:18,120 --> 00:07:22,279
he would only fool around like a kid and wouldn't cross the line.

116
00:07:22,279 --> 00:07:23,279
But look at what happened now.

117
00:07:23,279 --> 00:07:24,920
You're badly hurt.

118
00:07:25,240 --> 00:07:26,240
It has nothing to do with him.

119
00:07:26,439 --> 00:07:27,480
Lan Qi.

120
00:07:27,839 --> 00:07:29,079
I'm begging you.

121
00:07:29,560 --> 00:07:31,759
You really have to help Shi Yi.

122
00:07:31,759 --> 00:07:33,639
She can't work as a bodyguard anymore.

123
00:07:33,639 --> 00:07:35,240
I can't bear to see my daughter...

124
00:07:35,240 --> 00:07:37,360
risking her life for someone else's son.

125
00:07:37,560 --> 00:07:39,279
It's my job, Mom.

126
00:07:39,279 --> 00:07:42,160
I don't care. Resign right now!

127
00:07:42,160 --> 00:07:43,800
How can I simply resign?

128
00:07:43,800 --> 00:07:45,000
Say something!

129
00:07:45,000 --> 00:07:46,680
You stop talking when it's your turn to talk.

130
00:07:46,680 --> 00:07:48,600
- Tell her to resign now! - Shi Yi.

131
00:07:48,600 --> 00:07:49,639
If you have any situation,

132
00:07:49,639 --> 00:07:51,279
- just tell your mom. - Don't argue with the elders.

133
00:07:51,279 --> 00:07:52,279
It's pointless.

134
00:07:52,480 --> 00:07:53,560
You must resign.

135
00:08:47,330 --> 00:08:49,039
Shi Yi is working too hard.

136
00:08:49,210 --> 00:08:51,450
We must stop her from working as a bodyguard.

137
00:08:55,879 --> 00:08:56,879
Listen, Ying Nan.

138
00:08:57,330 --> 00:08:59,720
At the time when Shi Yi was righteous and courageous,

139
00:08:59,879 --> 00:09:01,360
you were so proud of her.

140
00:09:01,679 --> 00:09:03,210
You stood up straight and held your head high.

141
00:09:03,559 --> 00:09:05,330
You were quite excited back then.

142
00:09:05,519 --> 00:09:07,120
When robbers were nowhere to be seen,

143
00:09:07,120 --> 00:09:09,450
you always hoped that she'd have a chance to run into them.

144
00:09:09,600 --> 00:09:10,799
How is that the same?

145
00:09:11,480 --> 00:09:13,279
That was justice.

146
00:09:13,279 --> 00:09:15,210
She was protecting the people and their assets.

147
00:09:15,210 --> 00:09:16,639
Of course I would be proud and honored.

148
00:09:17,840 --> 00:09:19,090
What's the difference?

149
00:09:20,039 --> 00:09:21,559
Shi Yi saved Hou Jue's life.

150
00:09:21,840 --> 00:09:23,039
Even if it's not an honor,

151
00:09:23,480 --> 00:09:24,799
at least it's a virtue.

152
00:09:25,279 --> 00:09:28,639
But don't you think it's too risky?

153
00:09:34,480 --> 00:09:35,559
I'm telling you.

154
00:09:36,210 --> 00:09:37,330
Speaking of danger,

155
00:09:38,159 --> 00:09:41,240
it's the safest to be a bodyguard in our country.

156
00:09:41,879 --> 00:09:43,519
We have fewer criminals here.

157
00:09:44,039 --> 00:09:45,039
Try to do that in some other countries.

158
00:09:45,279 --> 00:09:46,360
Now, that's really dangerous.

159
00:09:50,279 --> 00:09:51,330
You're cold-hearted.

160
00:09:54,039 --> 00:09:56,360
We're not compatible. I'm hanging up.

161
00:10:11,330 --> 00:10:14,159
I'm just passionate. Yes, we don't agree on anything.

162
00:10:14,159 --> 00:10:16,450
Get some rest.

163
00:10:32,210 --> 00:10:33,210
Thank you.

164
00:10:34,639 --> 00:10:35,639
Is this where you live?

165
00:10:36,639 --> 00:10:38,120
Yes, this is it.

166
00:10:40,000 --> 00:10:41,559
Don't be too hard on yourself.

167
00:10:41,559 --> 00:10:43,360
(Xing and Eight Guests)

168
00:10:43,360 --> 00:10:44,559
No, I like it here.

169
00:10:45,720 --> 00:10:47,960
Something has changed with the client.

170
00:10:47,960 --> 00:10:49,450
It's just temporary.

171
00:10:51,919 --> 00:10:52,960
All right.

172
00:10:54,120 --> 00:10:56,720
Ms. Zhang was angry today.

173
00:10:56,919 --> 00:10:58,440
Don't take it to heart.

174
00:10:58,639 --> 00:10:59,799
She's just worried about you.

175
00:11:00,879 --> 00:11:03,720
They won't listen to you at the moment.

176
00:11:04,080 --> 00:11:05,159
Take your time.

177
00:11:06,519 --> 00:11:07,960
I need this job.

178
00:11:07,960 --> 00:11:09,200
And I love what I do.

179
00:11:09,639 --> 00:11:10,679
I won't quit.

180
00:11:12,600 --> 00:11:13,679
I understand.

181
00:11:14,919 --> 00:11:16,960
You haven't changed one bit after all these years.

182
00:11:17,360 --> 00:11:18,720
You're still passionate.

183
00:11:19,639 --> 00:11:20,799
Actually,

184
00:11:21,960 --> 00:11:23,279
I'm proud of you.

185
00:11:26,039 --> 00:11:27,039
By the way,

186
00:11:27,200 --> 00:11:30,879
don't tell my parents about Hou Jue's situation yet.

187
00:11:31,080 --> 00:11:32,799
I'm afraid of causing unnecessary trouble.

188
00:11:34,840 --> 00:11:35,919
Don't worry.

189
00:11:38,440 --> 00:11:39,519
Does the wound still hurt?

190
00:11:41,000 --> 00:11:42,039
It's okay.

191
00:11:42,039 --> 00:11:43,080
It's recovering well.

192
00:11:45,159 --> 00:11:46,279
Be careful.

193
00:11:49,039 --> 00:11:50,039
Drive slowly.

194
00:11:51,120 --> 00:11:52,519
Get some rest. Good night.

195
00:11:52,519 --> 00:11:53,519
Bye.

196
00:12:02,960 --> 00:12:04,000
Why are you standing here?

197
00:12:04,320 --> 00:12:05,879
What a nice chat.

198
00:12:05,879 --> 00:12:07,159
I didn't know you were so talkative.

199
00:12:09,279 --> 00:12:10,600
We had a good chat indeed.

200
00:12:11,000 --> 00:12:12,120
Did you talk about getting married?

201
00:12:14,200 --> 00:12:15,440
Yes, we talked about that.

202
00:12:16,159 --> 00:12:18,720
But I don't know when exactly.

203
00:12:18,919 --> 00:12:20,000
I'll let you know when it's confirmed.

204
00:12:20,879 --> 00:12:21,919
Good night.

205
00:12:32,480 --> 00:12:33,679
Don't be mad.

206
00:13:03,440 --> 00:13:04,440
Here, Mr. Ma.

207
00:13:09,879 --> 00:13:10,960
Mr. Ma.

208
00:13:11,559 --> 00:13:12,919
Thank you for trusting us.

209
00:13:13,840 --> 00:13:15,240
From now on, whenever you need us,

210
00:13:15,879 --> 00:13:18,600
we'll do our best in providing our security services.

211
00:13:18,840 --> 00:13:20,159
Thank you, Mr. Zhao.

212
00:13:20,480 --> 00:13:22,519
You trained her to be a great employee.

213
00:13:22,519 --> 00:13:24,039
It has been great working together.

214
00:13:24,200 --> 00:13:27,000
Since our contract has been terminated,

215
00:13:27,399 --> 00:13:29,679
that means Wu Shi Yi is free now.

216
00:13:30,159 --> 00:13:31,159
Okay.

217
00:13:31,159 --> 00:13:34,399
Mr. Zhao, let's sign my contract with Shi Yi quickly.

218
00:13:35,600 --> 00:13:37,080
Why are you in such a hurry, Mr. Hou Junior?

219
00:13:37,279 --> 00:13:39,000
Why did I bring Mr. Ma here?

220
00:13:39,000 --> 00:13:40,200
It's for a seamless transition.

221
00:13:40,200 --> 00:13:41,200
Let's sign the contract now.

222
00:13:41,559 --> 00:13:42,759
Mr. Hou Junior.

223
00:13:42,919 --> 00:13:44,759
You're so thoughtful.

224
00:13:45,639 --> 00:13:47,240
Excuse me, Mr. Zhao.

225
00:13:47,480 --> 00:13:49,639
- Please. - I'll see myself out.

226
00:13:50,000 --> 00:13:51,000
Take care.

227
00:13:54,879 --> 00:13:56,320
After you left,

228
00:13:57,039 --> 00:13:59,440
your dad has been in a bad mood and unwell.

229
00:13:59,879 --> 00:14:02,559
He has aged so much.

230
00:14:02,919 --> 00:14:04,639
It's heartbreaking.

231
00:14:06,919 --> 00:14:07,960
Actually,

232
00:14:08,559 --> 00:14:11,039
you're his only emotional support.

233
00:14:12,360 --> 00:14:13,840
Go see him when you have the time.

234
00:14:13,840 --> 00:14:14,879
Give him some comfort.

235
00:14:15,960 --> 00:14:16,960
Okay.

236
00:14:17,120 --> 00:14:19,240
I know what to do.

237
00:14:19,360 --> 00:14:20,399
Don't worry.

238
00:14:23,000 --> 00:14:24,919
A father and son can't be at odds forever.

239
00:14:35,440 --> 00:14:37,440
Let's sign the contract, Mr. Zhao.

240
00:14:37,440 --> 00:14:38,879
Okay, I even have a pen and paper ready for you.

241
00:14:39,039 --> 00:14:40,120
Take a look.

242
00:14:43,320 --> 00:14:44,440
Mr. Lan.

243
00:14:46,919 --> 00:14:48,840
- Welcome. - Hello, Mr. Zhao.

